cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MA 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with wireless sensor networks and their connectivity. 
2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of random geometric graphs and a new vertex-based random connection model. 
3. cs.IT (Information Theory) is a possibility as the paper may involve information theoretic concepts in determining the optimal transmission radius. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possibility as the paper may involve control theory concepts in designing the minimum-radius duty-cycling scheme. 
5. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) is a possibility as the paper may involve the coordination of multiple agents (sensors) in achieving connectivity.
